From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 04:57:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] cameraserver: relax VideoNativeHandleMetadata size validation
 for legacy HALs

Legacy Exynos camera HALs produce custom 20-byte metadata buffers for video recording instead of the standard 8-byte VideoNativeHandleMetadata structures. In CameraClient and CameraHardwareInterface, the strict equality checks (`size == sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)`) were causing the framework to silently reject and drop valid video frame buffers originating from the legacy Exynos wrapper.

This commit relaxes the rigid size validation from strict equality (`==` and `!=`) to relational checks (`>=` and `<`). This allows the 20-byte Exynos buffers to cleanly pass through the cameraserver pipeline without being dropped, restoring Zero-Copy Native Handle sharing for older devices.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: If08504110ecfa24f6f7307c1006bc813f99728be
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 services/camera/libcameraservice/api1/CameraClient.cpp    | 8 ++++----
 .../libcameraservice/device1/CameraHardwareInterface.cpp  | 4 ++--
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/services/camera/libcameraservice/api1/CameraClient.cpp b/services/camera/libcameraservice/api1/CameraClient.cpp
index 43da23eabc..9abbbb40e4 100644
--- a/services/camera/libcameraservice/api1/CameraClient.cpp
+++ b/services/camera/libcameraservice/api1/CameraClient.cpp
@@ -528,7 +528,7 @@ void CameraClient::releaseRecordingFrameHandle(native_handle_t *handle) {
         native_handle_close(handle);
         native_handle_delete(handle);
         return;
-    } else if (dataPtr->size() != sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+    } else if (dataPtr->size() < sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
         ALOGE("%s: %d: Callback buffer size doesn't match VideoNativeHandleMetadata", __FUNCTION__,
                 __LINE__);
         native_handle_close(handle);
@@ -568,7 +568,7 @@ void CameraClient::releaseRecordingFrameHandleBatch(const std::vector<native_han
                     __LINE__);
             error = true;
             break;
-        } else if (dataPtr->size() != sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+        } else if (dataPtr->size() < sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
             ALOGE("%s: %d: Callback buffer must be VideoNativeHandleMetadata", __FUNCTION__,
                     __LINE__);
             error = true;
@@ -933,7 +933,7 @@ void CameraClient::handleCallbackTimestampBatch(
         handles.reserve(n);
         for (auto& msg : msgs) {
             native_handle_t* handle = nullptr;
-            if (msg.dataPtr->size() != sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+            if (msg.dataPtr->size() < sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
                 ALOGE("%s: dataPtr does not contain VideoNativeHandleMetadata!", __FUNCTION__);
                 return;
             }
@@ -1105,7 +1105,7 @@ void CameraClient::handleGenericDataTimestamp(nsecs_t timestamp,
         native_handle_t* handle = nullptr;
 
         // Check if dataPtr contains a VideoNativeHandleMetadata.
-        if (dataPtr->size() == sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+        if (dataPtr->size() >= sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
             // TODO: Using unsecurePointer() has some associated security pitfalls
             //       (see declaration for details).
             //       Either document why it is safe in this case or address the
